channel.title: Music
channel.description: Is there a way i can get the music from Runescape? Not for my own personal collection i can assure you, but i have never been much of a runescape client hacker and as such have little or no knowledge on this subject. So if someone could oblige - in leymans terms preferably - would be much appreciated

item.title: Music
item.dc:creator: @ry60003333 ry60003333
item.description:
@ry60003333 wrote:

I am very sure that they are still in the MIDI format, Jagex is just using their own soundbank so it sounds the same on every OS/soundcard. Also, the music is loaded on demand. Try playing some music with the music packet in a 508 client, besides the login music, Harmony, and Autumn Voyage, the client will connect to the server with an update server request for the music. And in the 317 cache most of the music is missing also.

Read full topic

So if anyone has an account with ALL the songs please go on it, click on each song then extract the cache with cache extractor and send me the sound files please

On another topic

Do you want the old midis though? http://xcit.gotdns.com/files/rs_midi_tracks.rar

item.title: Music
item.dc:creator: @qauters qauters
item.description:
@qauters wrote:

Current sounds aren’t in midi formats anymore. There was an update a couple of months ago, where Jagex told that they made all sounds sound the same on every computer instead of different on every computer because it was created by the sound card in the past (midi).

If you want them, just get a deob and figure out where there sound system is located. Then find out how they load it and dump it
